2500|$|Branco and Rodrigues (2007) {{describe}} the stakeholder perspective of CSR as {{the set of}} views of corporate responsibility held by all groups or constituents with a relationship to the firm. In their <b>normative</b> <b>model</b> the company accepts these views {{as long as they}} do not hinder the organization. The stakeholder perspective fails to acknowledge the complexity of network interactions that can occur in cross-sector partnerships. It relegates communication to a maintenance function, similar to the exchange [...] perspective.|$|E
